## Biased Ruler — Methodology Clarification

In MAMA-MIA, every image had both a gold and a silver label, so the biased ruler
experiment was straightforward: evaluate the same model against both rulers. In
CSpineSeg, each image has either gold or silver — not both.

**Adapted approach:** Use the global model (Dataset001, trained on gold + silver) to
generate predictions on the gold-labeled test images. Those predictions serve as the
"silver labels" for those images. Now both rulers exist for the same set of images:

- Evaluate Dataset001 against **gold labels** → true performance
- Evaluate Dataset001 against **model-generated predictions** (as silver ruler) → observed performance

Compare the fairness gap between the two. Any difference is the pure ruler effect.

